<p style="background-color:powderblue;">Standard, predefined color names be used to indicate colors.</p>

<p style="color:rgb(200,20,200);">RGB values can be used to specify a color based on the proportions of red, green, and blue light to be emitted by the screen.</p>

<p style="color:rgba(200,20,200,0.5);">RGB values include an additional value (alpha) for transparency.</p>

<p style="color:#b814b8;">RGB values, which range from 0-255 in the decimal number system, can be described w/ 6 hexadecimal characters in. These are HEX values.</p>

<p style="border:2px solid hsl(90,80%,30%)">HSL values allow for describing other color qualities. H is hue (as a degree on the color wheel), S is saturation (where 0% is gray) and L is lightness (where 0% is white and 100% is black).</p>

<p style="border:2px solid hsla(90,80%,30%,0.5)">HSLA values include an additional value (alpha) for transparency.</p>


